.TH "add_taint" 9 "add_taint" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
add_taint \- add a taint flag if not already set.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" add_taint
.BI "(unsigned flag "  ","
.BI "enum lockdep_ok lockdep_ok "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "flag" 12
one of the TAINT_* constants.
.IP "lockdep_ok" 12
whether lock debugging is still OK.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
If something bad has gone wrong, you'll want \fIlockdebug_ok\fP = false, but for
some notewortht-but-not-corrupting cases, it can be set to true.
